Codeforces 144A–Arrival of the General

Problem

Given the heights of soldiers in a line, arrange them so that:

The tallest soldier is at the front (index 0).

The shortest soldier is at the end (index n-1).
You can swap adjacent soldiers, each swap taking 1 second.
Find the minimum time required.

---

Approach

1. Find the first occurrence of the maximum height → maxPos.


2. Find the last occurrence of the minimum height → minPos.


3. Calculate:

swaps = maxPos + (n - 1 - minPos)
if maxPos > minPos:
    swaps -= 1

---

Code (C)

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int n, i, maxPos = 0, minPos = 0;
    scanf("%d", &n);
    int a[n];
    for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        scanf("%d", &a[i]);
        if (a[i] > a[maxPos]) maxPos = i;
        if (a[i] <= a[minPos]) minPos = i;
    }
    int swaps = maxPos + (n - 1 - minPos);
    if (maxPos > minPos) swaps--;
    printf("%d\n", swaps);
    return 0;
}

Example

Input:

7
10 10 58 31 63 40 76

Output:

10

Explanation:

maxPos = 6 (76), minPos = 1 (last 10)

swaps = 6 + (7 - 1 - 1) = 11 → maxPos > minPos → 10.

